<img src="http://c.biz-file.com/c/1712/422868-625x325.jpg?2" alt="Properbuz grows to over 700,000 listings" width="625" height="325">© Ivan Kruk – 123RF.comThe service is connected to Bebuzee, a social platform that includes video, photos, blogs and a sharing network, and is the brain child of Joe Onyero. “We seamlessly connect the millions of Bebuzee.com users to our built-in Properbuz service allowing them to search for properties to rent or purchase near their homes or in other places in the world. We call it 'social property searching' and make it an enjoyable activity for our users that combines results with social outreach,” explains Onyero. <img src="http://c.biz-file.com/c/1711/418377-120x120.jpg?2" alt="New app launched to connect people to places to work" width="120" height="120">New app launched to connect people to places to workThree South African entrepreneurs recently launched an app that connects people to places to work, collaborate and network...14 Nov 2017Bebuzee users are able to follow estate agents, properties and regions of interest on a dashboard, creating a “followers club”, and add reviews. The Properbuz search function includes GPS mapping, social networking, and fan-based features.